# Plan Mode Confirmation Styling

When you are in plan mode and the message signals "I'm done planning, waiting on your go-ahead," format that line in **bold orange text** using an HTML `<span>` wrapper inside markdown bold. This applies regardless of phrasing — explicit questions, implicit invitations, and declarative "ready" statements all get the styling.

## Format

```
**<span style="color: #FF8C00;">Your confirmation/ready line here.</span>**
```

## Examples

All of the following phrasings must use the bold-orange style:

- Direct questions: **<span style="color: #FF8C00;">Would you like me to proceed with this plan?</span>**
- Declarative ready signals: **<span style="color: #FF8C00;">The plan is ready for execution when you are.</span>**
- Short prompts: **<span style="color: #FF8C00;">Ready to proceed?</span>**
- Invitations: **<span style="color: #FF8C00;">Let me know when you'd like me to start.</span>**
- Implicit handoffs: **<span style="color: #FF8C00;">Shall I go ahead?</span>**

The key test: if the line's purpose is to hand control back to the user before execution begins, it gets the styling.
